        <h3><strong>Tokenized Field Sections as NFTs</strong></h3>
        <p>
          Fan Game Cube transforms stadium fields into ownable digital territory by dividing them into distinct NFT sections. Each section represents specific coordinates on the playing field, creating a direct connection between fans and the physical space where their favorite sports unfold.
        </p>
        <p>
          Fans purchase these NFT sections strategically, targeting areas where critical game action is likely to occur. The platform supports football, chess, tennis, and cricket, with each sport featuring its own tailored coordinate system that reflects natural gameplay patterns.
        </p>
        <p>
          This tokenization model turns static viewing into strategic ownership. <a href="https://docs.bws.ninja/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fan Game Cube documentation</a> provides detailed specifications for how each sport's field is mapped and tokenized, ensuring fans understand exactly what territory they're claiming.
        </p>
        <h3><strong>Reward Generation from Game Events</strong></h3>
        <p>
          Ownership becomes valuable the moment game action enters your territory. When events unfold at owned coordinates, the corresponding NFT automatically generates rewards, transforming each play into a potential earning opportunity.
        </p>
        <p>
          The system continuously tracks live game events in real-time, instantly identifying which NFT owners should receive rewards based on where the action occurs. This creates an unprecedented connection between real-world sports moments and fan participation, making every goal, serve, checkmate, or boundary delivery personally meaningful.
        </p>
        <p>
          Reward mechanisms are calibrated differently for each sport to reflect their unique dynamics. High-scoring sports like cricket distribute rewards more frequently, while strategic games like chess offer premium rewards for critical squares where decisive moves typically happen.
        </p>
        <h3><strong>New Revenue Streams for Clubs</strong></h3>
        <p>
          While fans gain new ways to engage, sports organizations unlock entirely new revenue opportunities through blockchain integration. The platform enables clubs to monetize digital field sections without disrupting traditional ticketing, broadcasting, or sponsorship models.
        </p>
        <p>
          Clubs benefit immediately from initial NFT sales, then continue earning through secondary market transaction fees as fans trade sections based on strategic value and team performance. This creates sustainable revenue that grows alongside fan engagement rather than competing with existing income streams.
        </p>
        <p>
